---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Controlled Architecture Evaluation | BeaconGuard Assurance"
  description="For healthcare, financial services, and regulated enterprise teams evaluating AI workflow control before model execution."
>
  <section>
    <h1>Controlled Architecture Evaluation</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      For healthcare, financial services, and regulated enterprise teams evaluating AI workflow control before model execution.
    </p>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is seeking bounded architecture reviews with teams that own regulated workflows where AI requests need deterministic policy enforcement, approved-pathway checks, needs-review routing, or audit-ready evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Not a Rip-and-Replace Proposal</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard does not replace existing enterprise applications. The evaluation should focus on whether an existing workflow can be made fail-closed, policy-controlled, and auditable at the AI request boundary.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Evaluation Format</h2>
    <p>
      For innovation offices, this may operate as a design-partner discussion. For CIO, CISO, privacy, compliance, and architecture teams, the intended format is a controlled technical validation review.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Who Should Participate</h2>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--compact">
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Healthcare AI Control Architecture Review</h3>
        <p>Healthcare privacy, security, clinical informatics, digital health, compliance, audit, and hospital operations technology teams.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Financial Workflow Review</h3>
        <p>AML platform, financial crime engineering, fraud technology, risk, compliance, and security architecture teams.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="content-card">
        <h3>Regulated Internal Automation Review</h3>
        <p>IT operations, platform engineering, enterprise architecture, and internal tooling teams evaluating AI agents or automations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What We Validate Together</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Where the AI request boundary exists in the current workflow</li>
      <li>Which existing systems remain authoritative for workflow logic and records</li>
      <li>Which signed request metadata, workflow identity, user role, source-system trust, context tags, freshness windows, and approved-pathway inputs are available</li>
      <li>Which actions should return allow, deny, or needs-review</li>
      <li>What audit-ready evidence reviewers need after each decision</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Contact the team</h2>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/contact">Request Controlled Architecture Evaluation</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/platform">Review platform overview</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
